i’ve spent a lot of time spending a lot of time; chasing temporary hits + avoiding all the big and small things + trying with such effort while barely moving from one place. small tasks (sometimes) feeling hard and big tasks (often) feeling impossible. i’m forever peeling back the layers and coming home to myself. what a relief to be able to name this layer after feeling its weight for so long. the biggest burden lifted. turns out it’s been weaving through my lyrics all along, just waiting for me to connect the dots.

the feeling / the energy around the feeling / time 🍃

when the path you’re carving brings you back to your roots.

Oops, I lost that specific energy I need to feel comfortable taking up space here on social media. But I’ve been wading through murky feelings, and carving new lyrics from the debris. And I wanna sing them out loud.
 
12 new songs. And it’s gonna be FUN! I’m very done chasing the algorithm and following the social media strategies and rules. 🫠 I lose my authenticity when I chase traction, even though I’m sharing authentic content.
 
So I’m shifting direction + comin back to my roots. Ding! Let’s play. 🌱🍃
